- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: With ~12 V confirmed at Control Module 1 input, and all switches set to ON, sequentially measure the voltage across each control module’s indicator LED (anode to cathode) and across its internal switch terminals. For each module, verify: (1) that ~12 V is present between its incoming 12 V and 0 V lines, (2) that the switch closes (near‑0 Ω/contact voltage drop when ON) and passes 12 V to the next module, and (3) whether the LED branch actually sees ~12 V (or at least several volts) or is open/shorted. Record for each module whether 12 V reaches its input, its LED, and its output toward the next module.
